			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm thinking the timing occasionally creates a bus conflict (or some other glitch) when reloading the horizontal scroll bits at x=257. Bus conflicts in NMOS tend to use AND logic, as seen in SAX instruction and <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=109708#p109708" class="postlink">discrete logic mappers</a>, which produces a preponderance of zero bits. Games that don't scroll horizontally are already more likely to leave a zero in the horizontal scroll bits.<br /><br />Implication for developers: This could be another reason why games need a timeout on their sprite 0 wait routines. The simplest timeout increases the sprite 0 jitter from 7 cycles (bit/bvc) to 9 (bit/bmi/bvc).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
